    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="246" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hicks</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima, Peru</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20,
                                    1889</hi>
                        </date>. (Received January 14, 1890.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 56.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch, No. 49, of
                            November 14, 1889, regarding the claim of the Hydrographic Commission, I
                            have the honor here with to transmit the reply of the Peruvian foreign
                            office to my note of November 5, and a translation of the same.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hicks.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No.
                                    56—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Yrigoyen</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Ricks</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-11-23">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 23,
                                        1889</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 20.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to the attentive note of your
                                excellency of the 5th instant, I have the honor to state that I have
                                asked for the necessary information from the ministry of finance,
                                and that as soon as received it will be transmitted to your
                                excellency.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">M. Yrigoyen.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
